name: Laminum Album - Naturally BW
description: A squared crop on a photo I made in the woods nearby a river pretty casually, but turned out cooler than I imagined. To capture this picture I used my phone's camera set to pro mode so that I could control basic parameters. Everything was in shadow except from certain areas due to the above foliage. This plant in particular was in the focus of light, but I wanted to focus on it even more. I used the following parameters: F1,8 | 1/750 s | 5,23mm | ISO 200. The picture curiously turned out BW in the brigther areas. Maybe this is a common phenomenon, well known by pro photographers, but for me it's been the first time. I could have edited the photo some way but didn't want to ruin the magic that naturally happened. I didn't even change the file name so that everything stayed intact.
